                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51/340: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kornfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-05-15T16:00:00+03:25">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1924—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 15—10:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>40. British Government has telegraphed its Chargé here that it cannot consent to
                    hypothecation of Anglo-Persian royalties and southern customs for loan in United
                    States before a settlement has been reached concerning Persian debts to Great
                    Britain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kornfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
